# ibinet-sdk Implementation Guardrails

- Prefer backward-compatible changes because multiple applications consume this package directly.
- When editing models, keep relationships, casts, and key conventions stable unless migration strategy is explicit.
- Keep helpers small and composable; avoid introducing app-coupled assumptions.
- For shared services, preserve approval and technician-borrow flow contracts and status transitions.
- Validate new behavior against cross-app usage patterns before refactors.
